{"version":"https://jsonfeed.org/version/1.1","title":"TryHackMe - Collection | ꜱᴘᴀᴡɴ𝟐ᴘᴡɴ","description":"Personal CTF writeups and cybersecurity notes.","home_page_url":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/ctf-writeups/","language":"en","icon":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/apple-touch-icon.png","favicon":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/favicon.ico","authors":[{"name":"spawn2pwn","url":"https://github.com/nfl-alvis","avatar":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/images/IdaWin.png"}],"items":[{"title":"Lo-Fi","date_published":"2026-07-02T00:00:00&#43;08:00","date_modified":"2026-07-05T18:05:42&#43;07:00","id":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/","url":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/","authors":[{"name":"spawn2pwn","url":"https://github.com/nfl-alvis","avatar":"https://gravatar.loli.net/avatar/b01c9af4b33ead25b072a03f8d0c5508?s=32&amp;d=mp"}],"tags":["Local File Inclusion"],"summary":" Want to hear some lo-fi beats while relaxing or studying? We\u0026rsquo;ve got you covered!\nTL;DR Lo-Fi is an easy TryHackMe room that demonstrates a Local File Inclusion (LFI) vulnerability. By exploiting the vulnerable page parameter, it is possible to read arbitrary files from the server, including /etc/passwd. 5 Overview The target provides a web application with a simple interface.\n","content_html":"\u003ca class=\"lightgallery\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/images/room_image.webp\" title=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/images/room_image.webp\" data-thumbnail=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/images/room_image.webp\" data-sub-html=\"\u003ch2\u003e/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/images/room_image.webp\u003c/h2\u003e\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" src='/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/images/room_image.webp' alt=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/images/room_image.webp\" height=\"600\" width=\"1200\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWant to hear some lo-fi beats while relaxing or studying? We\u0026rsquo;ve got you covered!\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"details admonition abstract open\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"details-summary admonition-title\"\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon fa-solid fa-clipboard-list\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003eTL;DR\u003ci class=\"details-icon fa-solid fa-angle-right\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"details-content\"\u003e\n      \u003cdiv class=\"admonition-content\"\u003eLo-Fi is an easy TryHackMe room that demonstrates a Local File Inclusion (LFI) vulnerability. By exploiting the vulnerable \u003ccode\u003epage\u003c/code\u003e parameter, it is possible to read arbitrary files from the server, including \u003ccode\u003e/etc/passwd\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 class=\"heading-element\" id=\"overview\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e5 Overview\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003ca href=\"#overview\" class=\"heading-mark\"\u003e\n    \u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n  \u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe target provides a web application with a simple interface.\u003c/p\u003e"}]}